                <para>
                    <title>Truck and Conventional Bus Service Information</title>
                </para>
                <para>The new upper oil pan assembly has eliminated the center bosses with mounting bolt holes found on
                    engines built before 2004 Model Year (see Figure 1).
                </para>
                <para>The new assembly is compatible with 2003 Model Year engines. The old mounting bolts (M6 x 25) can
                    be reused. The old center boss mounting bolts (M8 x 40) can be discarded.
                </para>
                <para>To install new upper oil pan assembly, follow procedures outlined in corresponding Model Year
                    Engine Service Manual. Installation procedures remain the same, with the exception of eliminating
                    center boss mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
            <geninfo>
                <para>A new production and service upper oil pan assembly was released for Truck, Rear Engine (RE) Bus,
                    Semi Forward Control (SFC) Bus, and Stripped Chassis VT 365 diesel engine applications.
                </para>
